result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicholis N Frost was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Nicholis N Frost in court with attorney Mark David Lawton.  Defendant Nicholis N Frost in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed and read-in. Atty Hendee states that the parties are not requesting a PSI.  Atty Lawton agrees.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  Count 2 to be dismissed and read-in.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Lawton makes sentencing arguments.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1:  Impose and Stay; 8 years in the Wisconsin State Prison System with 4 years Initial Confinement and 4 years Extended Supervision with conditions:
3 years Probation with conditions; consecutive to his current sentence from Outagamie County and Waushara County
Court Costs = $268.00
DNA Sample (if not done so already) + $250.00 Surcharge
Restitution = $2,094.06 + 10% Surcharge $209.40 = $2,303.46; joint and several with Alexander M Stanelle 15CF100 & Katrina M Gruber 15CF99
Eligible for Substance Abuse Program
Eligible for Challange Incarceration Program
Credit = 0 days
No PSI ordered
  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

Ct. 2 to be dismissed and read-in.
